# Governed renderer placement contract

**Canonical authority:** [ADR-0025](../../docs/decisions/0025-governed-renderer-placement-contract.md)

Three rules. Each closes a specific drift path. All three must hold in every PR that touches a renderer or its configuration schema.

---

## Rule 1 — Container queries, never viewport breakpoints

Viewport breakpoints (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) fire on the viewport width.
A renderer placed inside a narrow column will overflow even on a wide screen.

```tsx
// ❌ viewport-relative — breaks in any constrained container
<div className="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4">

// ✅ container-relative — correct at every placement
<section className="@container">
  <div className="grid grid-cols-2 @sm:grid-cols-4">
```

Every renderer that lays out children in a grid or flex row must declare `@container` on its
outermost element and use `@sm:` / `@md:` / `@lg:` / `@xl:` / `@2xl:` breakpoints.

Tailwind v4 container queries require no plugin — they are core.

---

## Rule 2 — Every configuration schema declares `dataNature`

Every non-container renderer schema must export a `dataNatureSchema` enum and require it as a
field in the configuration schema.

**Required exports for every renderer schema (ADR-0025 §2):**

```ts
// 1. Named enum
export const <name>DataNatureSchema = z.enum(["..."])
export type <Name>DataNature = z.infer<typeof <name>DataNatureSchema>

// 2. Field in configuration schema
export const <name>ConfigurationSchema = z
  .object({
    dataNature: <name>DataNatureSchema,   // required; add .default("...") for backwards compat only
    ...
  })
  .strict()
```

**Accepted data natures per renderer (AFENDA_GOVERNED_RENDERER_CONTRACTS in registry.ts):**

| Renderer | dataNatures |
|---|---|
| `stat-card` | `"kpi"` · `"snapshot-summary"` |
| `list-surface` | `"table"` · `"document-lines"` |
| `action-bar` | `"actions"` |
| `audit-panel` | `"audit-trail"` |
| `detail-tabs` | `"tabbed-detail"` |
| `chart` | `"time-series"` · `"categorical"` |
| `approval-timeline` | `"approval-flow"` |

`section` and `stack` are container-only and are exempt.

**Builder authoring gate:**

- `dataNature: "kpi"` → aggregated operational metric; `delta` field = trend annotation ("+5%", "−50 MYR")
- `dataNature: "snapshot-summary"` → document figure; `delta` field = contextual label or omit entirely; ISO dates and raw decimal strings are not valid display values
- Never mix natures in a single stat-card instance

---

## Rule 3 — No raw `<div>` at the tile or leaf level

Every leaf UI element (tile, row badge, status chip, value cell) must be a shadcn primitive
from `#components2/ui/*`. Structural wrappers (`<section>`, `<ul>`, `<li>`) are exempt.

```tsx
// ❌ raw div with ad-hoc geometry — diverges across renderers over time
<div className="flex flex-col gap-1 rounded-2xl border border-border/60 bg-card px-4 py-3.5 shadow-xs">
  <span className="text-[11px] font-medium ...">

// ✅ shadcn Card + token typography classes
import { Card, CardContent } from "#components2/ui/card"

<Card>
  <CardContent className="flex flex-col gap-1 p-4">
    <span className="text-label-small text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">
```

Variant geometry (padding, gap, font size) belongs in a `cva` table or a
`const VARIANT_CLASS: Record<SchemaEnum, string>` map — **never** as inline ad-hoc values.
Each map must be typed as `Record<SchemaEnum, string>` so TypeScript catches missing enum members.

```ts
// ✅ exhaustive map — new enum value = compile error in the renderer
const DENSITY_CLASS: Record<StatCardDensity, string> = {
  compact: "gap-0.5 p-3",
  comfortable: "gap-1 p-4",
}

// ❌ inline ternary — silently misses new enum values
className={density === "compact" ? "gap-0.5 p-3" : "gap-1 p-4"}
```

---

## Checklist — applies to every renderer PR

- [ ] Outermost layout element uses `@container`; no `sm:` / `md:` / `lg:` breakpoints inside renderer
- [ ] Configuration schema exports `dataNature` enum + field
- [ ] `dataNature` registered in `AFENDA_GOVERNED_RENDERER_CONTRACTS` in `registry.ts`
- [ ] `GovernedComponentSkeleton` has a `case` for the new renderer id
- [ ] All variant maps are typed as `Record<SchemaEnum, string>` — no inline ternaries
- [ ] No raw `<div>` at tile/leaf level — shadcn primitives from `#components2/ui/*`
- [ ] ESLint `pnpm exec eslint --max-warnings=0 components2/metadata/renderers/` passes
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes

